title: MQMâ€™s Nasir Hussain Qureshi wins PS- 65 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Muttahida Qaumi Movement (MQM), Nasir Hussain Qureshi has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-65, Hyderabad-6, by securing 23,184 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Shoaib Shoukat, Independent Candidate, who bagged votes 14,321.
Overall voters turn-out remained 35.03 percent.
